of March 2019, Arora portrays Kunal Kapadia in [[StarPlus]]'s ''[[Yeh Rishtey Hain Pyaar Ke]]''.\n\n== Early life ==\nBorn in [[Delhi]], Arora attended [[St. Columba's School, Delhi|St. Columba's School]] and later went to [[Sri Guru Gobind Singh College of Commerce]] at the [[University of Delhi]], for his undergraduate studies. In 2015 he was one of the winners of the ''[[Delhi Times]]'' Fresh Face of the Year. He was in college when he was selected for his television debut in 2017 and moved to [[Mumbai]] to pursue his career in acting.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/delhi/delhi-fresh-face-winner-bags-the-lead-in-a-tv-show/articleshow/60362886.cms|title=Delhi Fresh Face winner bags the lead in a TV show|date=5 September 2017|website=Times of India}}</ref>\n\n==Career==\n\nArora's television debut came in 2017 when he played Ahaan Dhanrajgir opposite [[Jannat Zubair Rahmani]] in [[Colors TV]]'s ''[[Tu Aashiqui]]''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://indianexpress-com.cdn.ampproject.org/v/s/indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/television/tu-aashiqui-actor-ritvik-aroras-valentines-day-woes-5057176/lite/?usqp=mq331AQCKAE=&amp_js_v=0.1|title=Tu Aashiqui actor Ritvik Arora\u2019s Valentine\u2019s Day woes {{!}} Entertainment News, The Indian Express|website=indianexpress-com.cdn.ampproject.org|access-date=2019-10-21}}</ref> It culminated in 2018. As of March 2019, he plays Kunal Rajvansh in the [[Star Plus]] series ''[[Yeh Rishtey Hain Pyaar Ke]]''.<ref name=\"t1\">{{Cite web|url=https://www-timesnownews-com.cdn.ampproject.org/v/s/www.timesnownews.com/amp/videos/zoom/telly-talk/ritvik-arora-kaveri-priyam-reveal-the-storyline-of-yeh-rishtey-hain-pyar-ke-exclusive/25420?usqp=mq331AQCKAE=&amp_js_v=0.1|title=Ritvik Arora & Kaveri Priyam REVEAL the storyline of Yeh Rishtey Hain Pyar Ke {{!}} Exclusive|website=www-timesnownews-com.cdn.ampproject.org|access-date=2019-10-21}}</ref>\n\n==Television==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|